  "prompt": "Do any of the Indian banks provide personalized gift cards where I can put a personalized image on the card?",
  "response": "Yes, several Indian banks offer personalized gift cards with the option to add your own image. Here's a breakdown of some options and things to consider:\n\n**Banks Known to Offer Personalized Gift Cards with Image Upload:**\n\n*   **HDFC Bank:** HDFC Bank allows you to personalize gift cards with your own photo or message through their website. They often have promotional offers on these cards.\n*   **ICICI Bank:** ICICI Bank also allows personalization on some of their gift card offerings. Check their website for the most up-to-date options and customization process.\n\n**How to Find Specific Offerings:**\n\n1.  **Visit Bank Websites:** Go to the official website of major Indian banks (SBI, HDFC, ICICI, Axis, Kotak Mahindra, etc.).\n\n2.  **Search for \"Gift Cards\" or \"Prepaid Cards\":**  Use the search function on the bank's website to find their gift card or prepaid card section.\n\n3.  **Look for \"Personalization\" or \"Customization\" Options:** Within the gift card section, carefully look for options like \"Personalized Gift Card,\" \"Custom Gift Card,\" or any wording that indicates the ability to add your own image.\n\n4.  **Check the FAQs and Terms & Conditions:** Before creating a personalized gift card, read the FAQs and Terms & Conditions carefully. This will tell you:\n\n    *   **Image Guidelines:**  They will specify acceptable image formats (e.g., JPEG, PNG), size limitations (in pixels or megabytes), and image content restrictions (e.g., no copyrighted material, no offensive content).\n    *   **Processing Time:**  How long it will take to create and ship the personalized card.\n    *   **Fees and Charges:**  Any additional fees for personalization.\n    *   **Validity and Usage:**  The expiry date of the gift card and where it can be used.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Availability:** While many banks *offer* personalized cards, availability can vary based on card type or promotional periods.  Check the bank's website for current availability.\n*   **Fees:**  There's usually an additional fee for personalization, on top of the card's value.\n*   **Image Quality:** Use a high-resolution image to ensure a good-quality print on the card.\n*   **Restrictions:** Banks have strict guidelines on the images you can use. Avoid anything offensive, copyrighted, or inappropriate.  The bank will likely reject images that violate their policies.\n*   **Processing Time:** Personalized cards take longer to process and deliver than standard gift cards.  Order well in advance, especially during holidays.\n*   **Alternatives:** If a specific bank doesn't offer image personalization, you could consider a bank gift card with a standard design and then create a separate personalized card or holder to present it in.\n\n**In summary, HDFC and ICICI are good starting points to check.  Always confirm directly with the bank through their website or customer service to get the most accurate and up-to-date information on their personalized gift card offerings.**\n",
